23 (b) Beginning with the 2027-2028 fiscal year and ending with the 2032-2033 fiscal year,
24 the Department of Public Instruction shall raise the monthly amounts for each step of the teacher
25 salary schedule each fiscal year by three and sixty-seven hundredths percent (3.67%).
26 (c) Beginning in the 2033-2034 fiscal year and annually thereafter, the Department of
27 Public Instruction shall raise the monthly amounts for each step of the teacher salary schedule
28 for each fiscal year by the sum of one plus the 12-month percent change in the second quarter
29 Employment Cost Index for elementary and secondary school workers as reported by the Federal
30 Bureau of Labor Statistics.
31 (d) Salary Supplements for Teachers Paid on This Salary Schedule. –
32 (1) Licensed teachers who have NBPTS certification shall receive a salary
33 supplement each month of twelve percent (12%) of their monthly salary on
34 the "A" salary schedule.
35 (2) Licensed teachers who are classified as "M" teachers shall receive a salary
36 supplement each month of ten percent (10%) of their monthly salary on the
37 "A" salary schedule.
38 (3) Licensed teachers with licensure based on academic preparation at the
39 six-year degree level shall receive a salary supplement of one hundred
40 twenty-six dollars ($126.00) per month in addition to the supplement provided
41 to them as "M" teachers.
42 (4) Licensed teachers with licensure based on academic preparation at the
43 doctoral degree level shall receive a salary supplement of two hundred
44 fifty-three dollars ($253.00) per month in addition to the supplement provided
45 to them as "M" teachers.
46 (5) Certified school nurses shall receive a salary supplement each month of ten
47 percent (10%) of their monthly salary on the "A" salary schedule.
48 (6) School counselors who are licensed as counselors at the master's degree level
49 or higher shall receive a salary supplement each month of one hundred dollars
50 ($100.00).
