29 amended by subsection (a) of this section, any eligible student who receives a scholarship
30 pursuant to Part 2A of Article 39 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes in the 2026-2027
31 school year shall be eligible to receive a scholarship in the 2027-2028 fiscal year. The award
32 shall be at the same amount the student received in the 2026-2027 school year.
33 SECTION 2.(e) Notwithstanding G.S. 115C-562.8 and any other provision of law
34 to the contrary, the unencumbered, nonrecurring funds available for the award of opportunity
35 scholarship grants pursuant to Part 2A of Article 39 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes at
36 the end of the 2025-2026 fiscal year that would otherwise be carried forward in the 2026-2027
37 fiscal year pursuant to G.S. 115C-562.8(d)(2) shall be reduced by the sum of one hundred fifty
38 million dollars ($150,000,000) in nonrecurring funds.
39 SECTION 2.(f) Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, the
40 funds appropriated for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to the Opportunity Scholarship Grant Fund
41 Reserve for the award of opportunity scholarship grants pursuant to Part 2A of Article 39 of
42 Chapter 115C of the General Statutes in the 2027-2028 fiscal year shall be reduced by the sum
43 of one hundred ten million dollars ($110,000,000) in recurring funds.
44 SECTION 2.(g) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies beginning
45 with applications for the award of scholarship grants in the 2027-2028 school year.
46
47 PART III. EFFECTIVE DATE
48 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
49 law.
